  "returns": "is_tensorpaddle.is_tensor(x:Any)→TypeGuard[Tensor][source]Tests whether input object is a paddle.Tensor.NoteAlias Support: The parameter nameobjcan be used as an alias forx. For example,is_tensor(obj=tensor_x)is equivalent tois_tensor(x=tensor_x).Parametersx(object) – Object to test. alias:obj.ReturnsA boolean value. True ifxis a paddle.Tensor, otherwise False.Examples>>>importpaddle>>>input1=paddle.rand(shape=[2,3,5],dtype='float32')>>>check=paddle.is_tensor(input1)>>>print(check)True>>>input3=[1,4]>>>check=paddle.is_tensor(input3)>>>print(check)False",
